he%20mounting%20risk%20of%20recession%2C%20which%20could%20see%20US%20interest%20rates%20cut%20as%20early%20as%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gloomier%20outlook%20for%20global%20growth%20kept%20oil%20prices%20under%20heavy%20pressure%2C%20following%20steep%20losses%20last%20week.%20Brent%20fell%20%242.12%20to%20%2463.46%20a%20barrel%2C%20while%20U.S.%20crude%20dived%20%242.05%20to%20%2459.94%20per%20barrel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20flight%20to%20safe%20havens%20saw%20Treasury%20futures%20surge%20a%20full%20point%2C%20a%20very%20rare%20move%20for%20Asian%20trade%2C%20while%20Fed%20fund%20futures%20jumped%20to%20price%20in%20an%20extra%20quarter-point%20rate%20cut%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarkets%20swung%20to%20imply%20around%20a%2063%20per%20cent%20chance%20the%20Fed%20could%20cut%20as%20soon%20as%20May%2C%20even%20though%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20on%20Friday%20said%20the%20central%20bank%20was%20in%20no%20hurry%20on%20rates%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Reuters%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYields%20on%2010-year%20Treasuries%20dropped%2010%20basis%20points%20to%203.897%20per%20cent%20amid%20the%20general%20flight%20from%20risk%20assets.%C2%A0That%20dovish%20turn%20saw%20the%20dollar%20slip%20another%200.9%20per%20cent%20on%20the%20safe-haven%20Japanese%20yen%20to%20145.59%20yen%2C%20while%20the%20euro%20held%20firm%20at%20%241.0955.%20The%20dollar%20shed%201.2%20per%20cent%20on%20the%20Swiss%20franc%20to%200.8501%2C%20while%20the%20trade-exposed%20Australian%20dollar%20dropped%20a%20further%200.7%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20gold%20was%20swept%20up%20in%20the%20selloff%2C%20easing%200.7%20per%20cent%20to%20%243%2C013%20an%20ounce.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20Administration%20Refuses%20To%20Back%20Down%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20showed%20no%20sign%20of%20backing%20away%20from%20its%20sweeping%20tariff%20plans%2C%20and%20China%20declared%20the%20markets%20had%20spoken%20on%20their%20retaliation%20through%20levies%20on%20US%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvestors%20had%20thought%20the%20loss%20of%20trillions%20of%20dollars%20in%20wealth%20and%20the%20likely%20body%20blow%20to%20the%20economy%20would%20make%20Trump%20reconsider%20his%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20size%20and%20disruptive%20impact%20of%20U.S.%20trade%20policies%2C%20if%20sustained%2C%20would%20be%20sufficient%20to%20tip%20a%20still%20healthy%20US%20and%20global%20expansion%20into%20recession%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bruce%20Kasman%2C%20head%20of%20economics%20at%20JPMorgan%2C%20putting%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20downturn%20at%2060%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20continue%20to%20expect%20a%20first%20Fed%20easing%20in%20June%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20we%20now%20think%20the%20Committee%20cuts%20at%20every%20meeting%20through%20January%2C%20bringing%20the%20top%20of%20the%20funds%20rate%20target%20range%20down%20to%203.0%20per%20cent.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnInvestors%20were%20also%20wagering%20that%20the%20imminent%20threat%20of%20recession%20would%20outweigh%20the%20likely%20upward%20shove%20to%20inflation%20from%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20consumer%20price%20figures%20out%20later%20this%20week%20are%20expected%20to%20show%20another%20rise%20of%200.3%20per%20cent%20for%20March%2C%20but%20analysts%20assume%20it%20is%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20before%20tariffs%20push%20prices%20sharply%20higher%2C%20for%20everything%20from%20food%20to%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERising%20costs%20will%20also%20put%20pressure%20on%20company%20profit%20margins%2C%20just%20as%20the%20earnings%20season%20gets%20underway%20with%20some%20of%20the%20big%20banks%20due%20on%20Friday.%20Around%2087%20per%20cent%20of%20US%20companies%20will%20report%20between%20April%2011%20and%20May%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20expect%20during%20upcoming%20quarterly%20earnings%20calls%20fewer%20companies%20than%20usual%20will%20provide%20forward%20guidance%20for%20both%202Q%20and%20full-year%202025%2C%26quot%3B%20analysts%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%20said%20in%20a%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRising%20tariff%20rates%20will%20force%20many%20companies%20to%20either%20raise%20prices%20or%20accept%20lower%20profit%20margins%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20warned.%20%26quot%3BWe%20expect%20negative%20revisions%20to%20consensus%20profit%20margin%20estimates%20in%20coming%20quarters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BBlack%20Monday%26quot%3B%20Fears%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESounding%20alarm%20bells%20after%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20Liberation%20Day%20global%20tariff%20plans%20crushed%20global%20stocks%20for%20two%20consecutive%20days%2C%20CNBC%20host%20Jim%20Cramer%20predicted%20global%20markets%20could%20witness%20a%20blood%20bath%20that%20could%20expand%20into%20a%20crash%20similar%20to%201987's%20%26quot%3BBlack%20Monday.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECramer%20said%20no%20matter%20what%20the%20numbers%20reveal%2C%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20market%20will%20depend%20on%20President%20Trump's%20next%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlack%20Monday%20was%20a%20global%20and%20largely%20unexpected%20stock%20market%20crash%20on%20Monday%2C%20October%2019%2C%201987.%20Worldwide%20losses%20were%20estimated%20at%20US%241.71%20trillion.%20The%20stock%20market's%20disastrous%20one-day%20tumble%20created%20a%20domino%20effect%20that%20caused%20the%20disaster%20to%20continue%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744000320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fgkcf8me_trump-afp_650x400_07_April_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fstock-market-today-nikkei-wall-street-sensex-nifty-50-australian-blue-chip-stocks-kospi-see-mega-tariff-shock-donald-trump-says-medicine-working-8104509%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Asian%20stock%20markets%20opened%20in%20a%20bloodbath%20on%20Monday%20as%2